```
import sys
from contextlib import contextmanager


def f():
    for x in iterator():
        pass

def iterator():
    with ctx():
        yield
    raise Exception()

@contextmanager
def ctx():
    yield


if __name__ == "__main__":
    try:
        f()
    except:
        import ipdb
        ipdb.post_mortem(sys.exc_info()[2])

```

When entering ipdb in the above example one cannot go up above `iterator`, i.e. to `f()`. Replacing `ipdb` with `pdb` works...

