- autobahn version 18.4.1

When transmitting an ApplicationError args and kwargs of original exception are included. It can be useful on the client side to also know the type of the exception.
So I would suggest to include the class name of the exception in autobahn.wamp.protocol.BaseSession._message_from_exception:

```
def _message_from_exception(self, request_type, request, exc, tb=None, enc_algo=None):
        """
        Create a WAMP error message from an exception.

        :param request_type: The request type this WAMP error message is for.
        :type request_type: int

        :param request: The request ID this WAMP error message is for.
        :type request: int

        :param exc: The exception.
        :type exc: Instance of :class:`Exception` or subclass thereof.

        :param tb: Optional traceback. If present, it'll be included with the WAMP error message.
        :type tb: list or None
        """
        args = None
        if hasattr(exc, 'args'):
            args = list(exc.args)  # make sure tuples are made into lists

        kwargs = None
        if hasattr(exc, 'kwargs'):
            kwargs = exc.kwargs

        if kwargs and six.PY2:
            kwargs = {
                k.decode('utf8'): v
                for k, v in kwargs.iteritems()
            }
            
        # begin
        # get class name of exception for later use
        if not isinstance( exc, exception.ApplicationError ):
            exc_type = str( exc.__class__ )
            
            import re
            # first search if 'class' in description
            reExcClass = re.compile( r"(?P<pre>\<class\s*)(?P<name>.+?)(?P<suf>\s*\>)" )
            # match "<class 'Modul.Exception'>" -> extract 'Modul.Exception'
            m = reExcClass.search( exc_type )
            if not m:
                # search for 'type' in description
                reExcType = re.compile( r"(?P<pre>\<class\s*)(?P<name>.+?)(?P<suf>\s*\>)" )
                # match "<type 'exceptions.ValueError'>" -> extract 'exceptions.ValueError'
                m = reExcType.search( exc_type ) 
            if m:
                exc_type = m.group( "name" )[1:-1]
            
                if kwargs:    
                    kwargs[u'error_class'] = exc_type
                else:
                    kwargs = { u'error_class': exc_type }
        # end

        if tb:
            if kwargs:
                kwargs[u'traceback'] = tb
            else:
                kwargs = {u'traceback': tb}
```

